1 olive oil
2 potato
1 Brown Onion
1 bag baby broccoli
2 tomato
2 bag herbs
½ lemon
1 packet walnuts
1 packet ciabatta
1 packet Lamb Shortloin
1 packet romesco sauce
1 drizzle red wine vinegar
¼ packet Cow's Milk Feta
3 clove garlic
1 sachet Berbere seasoning

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks. Cut onion
into wedges. Trim baby broccoli. Slice tomato
into wedges.
• Pick and roughly chop herb leaves. Slice lemon
into wedges. Roughly chop walnuts. Finely chop
garlic.

• Place potato and herbs on a lined oven tray,
then drizzle with olive oil and season with salt
and pepper. Toss to coat.
• In a baking dish, place tomato and onion.
Drizzle with olive oil, season and toss to coat.
Roast potatoes and veggies until tender and
golden, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: The baking dish helps collect all the roasted
tomato juices!

• While the veggies are roasting, cut or tear
ciabatta into chunks.
• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of
olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook ciabatta,
tossing, until golden, 5-6 minutes.
• Add another drizzle of olive oil and 1/2 the
garlic and cook, tossing, until fragrant,
1 minute. Transfer to a plate and season.

• In a medium bowl, combine Berbere seasoning
and a drizzle of olive oil. Add lamb shortloin,
season and turn to coat.
• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook lamb for 3-4 minutes
each side for medium or until cooked to your
liking. Transfer to a plate to rest for 5 minutes.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this
adds to the flavour!

• Meanwhile, heat a second large frying pan over
medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook baby broccoli with a splash of water until
softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add remaining garlic, a good squeeze of lemon
juice and the walnuts and cook, tossing, until
fragrant, 1 minute. Season, then transfer to a
serving dish.

• Slice smokey lamb.
• Add croutons and a drizzle of red wine vinegar
to the roasted tomato. Toss to combine, then
crumble over feta (see ingredients).
• On the serving plates, spread romesco sauce,
then top with some lamb and any resting juices.
• Serve with tomato-crouton toss, roasted herby
potatoes, walnut greens and any remaining
lemon wedges. Enjoy!